{"TopicId":196668,"ForumId":25,"TopicTitle":"Hydraulics failure landing","CreatedByName":"Pds314","CreatedById":70014,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-02T10:20:34Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Pds314","CreatedById":70014,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-02T10:20:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLand an aircraft that has suffered a total failure of all flight controls except the engine throttle. The craft must be an airworthy design and control \u0022failure\u0022 should begin at over 1500 meters above ground level.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cattette","CreatedById":206142,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-02T10:39:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs\u00A0engine gimbaling also not allowed?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Pds314","CreatedById":70014,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-02T10:41:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223847806\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022196668\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221599043170\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022206142\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Cattette\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Cattette said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs\u00A0engine gimbaling also not allowed?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt is not allowed. The only control alowed is engine thrust level.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"vyznev","CreatedById":90620,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-02T12:41:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere was \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/184399-fly-a-stock-plane-with-only-engine-thrust/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Ea similar challenge\u003C/a\u003E last year, except that it specifically required landing the stock Stearwing A300 plane. One person (\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/21456-silks/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002221456\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/21456-silks/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@silks\u003C/a\u003E) even managed to complete it. I might give it another try, just to see if I can do both challenges at once. \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022197002\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed7011058422\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/184399-fly-a-stock-plane-with-only-engine-thrust/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:214px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(Also, is using kOS allowed? Because I wrote \u003Ca href=\u0022https://gist.github.com/vyznev/75d82a5069c044358820959b6e854660\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ea kOS script for throttle-assisted steering\u003C/a\u003E a while ago. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(Ps. Just to check, is using thrust reversers allowed? I would assume no, if we\u0027re simulating a complete hydraulics failure, but I wanted to make sure.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-09-02T12:52:40Z\u0022 title=\u002209/02/2020 12:52  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 2, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by vyznev\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ralanboyle","CreatedById":201693,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-02T13:13:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/70014-pds314/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002270014\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/70014-pds314/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Pds314\u003C/a\u003E When you say \u0022aircraft\u0022 do you mean airplane (or spaceplace)?\u00A0Because a traditional pod w/ chute does this all the time.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"doggonemess","CreatedById":160106,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-02T13:38:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI was going to say, someone will take this literally and build a plane that can technically fly, then start at 1500 meters at 0 m/s and float down on four vertical engines.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThen they\u0027ll act smug and make faces.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00221zfc4o.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022122.55\u0022 height=\u0022250\u0022 width=\u0022204\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgflip.com/4/1zfc4o.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ralanboyle","CreatedById":201693,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-02T14:31:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOkay, so this is actually pretty easy. It did take me several tries to hit the runway but I\u00A0suppose that isn\u0027t required anyway. Really, you just need a stable airplane with big wheels to handle not flaring. I know there are also more complicated ways to accomplish the same thing. Perhaps we could have a scoring system to accommodate the harder stuff (like making it heavy).\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/twzpLJaDy-0?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sevenperforce","CreatedById":157695,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-02T20:48:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223847910\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022196668\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221599057113\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022201693\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ralanboyle\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, ralanboyle said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOkay, so this is actually pretty easy. It did take me several tries to hit the runway but I\u00A0suppose that isn\u0027t required anyway. Really, you just need a stable airplane with big wheels to handle not flaring. I know there are also more complicated ways to accomplish the same thing. Perhaps we could have a scoring system to accommodate the harder stuff (like making it heavy).\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot to gatekeep someone else\u0027s challenge but keeping \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E on is against the rules, right? Anything that actuates the control surfaces is forbidden.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-09-02T20:49:05Z\u0022 title=\u002209/02/2020 08:49  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 2, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by sevenperforce\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"vyznev","CreatedById":90620,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-02T22:44:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes a water landing count?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022rwE1Et3.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.25\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/rwE1Et3.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(And does it matter that I lost both engines and the nose cone on splashdown?)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Pds314","CreatedById":70014,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-02T23:44:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223847910\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022196668\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221599057113\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022201693\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ralanboyle\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, ralanboyle said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOkay, so this is actually pretty easy. It did take me several tries to hit the runway but I\u00A0suppose that isn\u0027t required anyway. Really, you just need a stable airplane with big wheels to handle not flaring. I know there are also more complicated ways to accomplish the same thing. Perhaps we could have a scoring system to accommodate the harder stuff (like making it heavy).\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/twzpLJaDy-0?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSadly you have used \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E, which manipulates the exact controls you\u0027re not supposed to use.\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223847841\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022196668\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221599050481\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002290620\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022vyznev\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 hours ago, vyznev said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere was \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/184399-fly-a-stock-plane-with-only-engine-thrust/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Ea similar challenge\u003C/a\u003E last year, except that it specifically required landing the stock Stearwing A300 plane. One person (\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/21456-silks/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002221456\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/21456-silks/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@silks\u003C/a\u003E) even managed to complete it. I might give it another try, just to see if I can do both challenges at once. \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022197002\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed6628660699\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/184399-fly-a-stock-plane-with-only-engine-thrust/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:213px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(Also, is using kOS allowed? Because I wrote \u003Ca href=\u0022https://gist.github.com/vyznev/75d82a5069c044358820959b6e854660\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ea kOS script for throttle-assisted steering\u003C/a\u003E a while ago. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(Ps. Just to check, is using thrust reversers allowed? I would assume no, if we\u0027re simulating a complete hydraulics failure, but I wanted to make sure.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKOS is fine I guess. As for thrust reversers, I think that\u0027ll be no.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ralanboyle","CreatedById":201693,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-03T01:48:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlright then, this isn\u0027t going to be pretty...\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/oMpJ_GJEN2k?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"vyznev","CreatedById":90620,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-03T03:13:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI finally did it \u2014 and completed \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/184399-fly-a-stock-plane-with-only-engine-thrust/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Elast year\u0027s challenge\u003C/a\u003E at the same time, too. Allow me to present to you a\u00A0perfect landing of the stock Stearwing A300 at \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E from 7000 m ASL using engine throttle control only. No \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E, no steering inputs, no kOS, Mechjeb or other mods*,\u00A0no action groups other than gears and brakes, no thrust reversers, no water landing and no lost parts or kerbal lives.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/kgkQHiuSf3U?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd it only took me three attempts to pull it off, too.**\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe trick seems to be flying really far away from the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E so that you\u0027ll have plenty of time to learn to control\u00A0the plane, find your heading, stabilize the altitude and line up a nice good and low approach. With this control method, \u003Cem\u003Enothing\u003C/em\u003E\u00A0happens quickly.*** You\u0027ll notice that most of the video is at 8x speed. In real time, the approach and landing took about half an hour, most of it\u00A0full of sweating and constantly adjusting multiple strongly coupled and lagged controls while monitoring the navball, the altimeter / vertical speed and the visual attitude of the plane itself (that being the most responsive indicator of which way the plane is about to pitch or roll).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:10px;\u0022\u003E*) Vessel mover was accidentally left open at the start of the run, but was only used to place the target marker at the end of the runway before the flight.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:10px;\u0022\u003E**) Plus at least two tries last year. Maybe more, I\u0027m not sure. But who\u0027s counting\u2026\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:10px;\u0022\u003E***) Except crashing. Crashing always happens quickly.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Pds314","CreatedById":70014,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-03T06:50:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223848225\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022196668\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221599097702\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022201693\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ralanboyle\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, ralanboyle said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlright then, this isn\u0027t going to be pretty...\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/oMpJ_GJEN2k?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI love it. Instead of making the aircraft controllable with engines you made it a flying tank.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ralanboyle","CreatedById":201693,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-03T12:02:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223848252\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022196668\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221599102809\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002290620\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022vyznev\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, vyznev said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI finally did it\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nepic\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}